@spec intervals_spec  src=tests/specs/intervals_spec.lua  loc=236  sha=922a349  cases=19
@exercises intervals (intervals)
@surface   intervals.seed, intervals.merge, intervals.intersects, intervals.close, intervals.absorbSeeds

# Intent
  intervals is the pure dirt-interval algebra (design/interval-dirt.md).
  A set is `true` (whole channel) or a ppqL-ascending, non-overlapping
  list of { loPpqL, hiPpqL, loUuid, hiUuid }. seed normalises; merge
  coalesces edge-inclusive and collapses to `true` past the cap;
  intersects is edge-inclusive; close widens each seed to its stage's
  anchoring onsets (forward always, back only under stepBack) without
  mutating its input.

# Helpers
  @fn evt(ppqL, uuid, lane, pitch)  @ 14-16
      -- An event as the closure consumes it: a logical position, a uuid anchor,
      -- and whatever fields opts.key groups on (lane, pitch).

# Cases
  @case 'seed normalises reversed bounds, swapping uuids with them'  [pure]  @ 25-30
  @case 'seed keeps a point interval degenerate'  [pure]  @ 34-38
  @case 'merge passes true through and leaves a singleton alone'  [pure]  @ 44-49
  @case 'merge coalesces overlapping and edge-touching intervals, keeping outer uuids'  [pure]  @ 53-65
  @case 'merge sorts before coalescing and does not mutate its input order'  [pure]  @ 69-75
  @case 'merge subsumes a fully-contained interval without extending the outer hi'  [pure]  @ 79-83
  @case 'merge collapses to true past the size cap'  [pure]  @ 87-92
  @case 'intersects is edge-inclusive and short-circuits on true'  [pure]  @ 98-104
  @case 'close passes true through'  [pure]  @ 110-113
  @case 'tails: stepBack widens to the previous and next same-pitch onset'  [pure]  @ 117-125
  @case 'tails: grouping picks the same-pitch neighbour, not the nearest onset'  [pure]  @ 129-138
  @case 'tails: a missing neighbour opens the edge toward the channel bound'  [pure]  @ 142-148
  @case 'forward closure holds the lower edge at the seed and steps only forward'  [pure]  @ 152-158
  @case 'close unions extensions across every group the interval touches'  [pure]  @ 162-172
  @case 'close steps in ppqL order -- delay-reordered raw is a phase-4 gap (design q5)'  [pure]  @ 176-192
  @case 'close does not mutate its input set'  [pure]  @ 196-202
  @case 'absorbSeeds narrows a seeded chan to its merged intervals'  [pure]  @ 208-215
  @case 'absorbSeeds folds an unseeded payload chan whole'  [pure]  @ 219-225
  @case 'absorbSeeds narrows a seeded chan even absent from the payload, overriding a prior true'  [pure]  @ 229-234

